    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAdd support for remote editing through ssh to Neovim.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAn interface which lets the user connect to a remote machine through ssh and edit files on it. ",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "potential outline:\n\n- user can select any \"host\" from their ssh config\n  - nvim should avoid _parsing_ ~./ssh/config as much as possible. instead it\n    should delegate almost everything to `ssh`. \"parsing\" may be needed to get\n    the list of host names (but maybe there's a way to ask `ssh` itself to give\n    us that list).\n  - show a menu. user can select from the menu.\n    - available as a `opt/` plugin. other plugins can use this to get a list of ssh host names.\n- connect to ssh endpoint\n  - system must have `ssh`. we will use that to connect.\n- reattach\n  - stop current nvim server without stopping the ui client. then \"reattach\" the ui client to the new remote nvim.\n      - hint: the `:restart` command in [#33953](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33953) (function `ui_client_event_restart`) is a great starting point.\n  - for reference, see the `:detach` impl:  https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/4b0e2605eaf90268195029a29f10903dc82729e7\n- auto-install on remote\n  - P0: auto-install nvim on the remote.\n  - P1: if remote outbound network doesn't work, download locally then upload to remote.\n  - P2: upload user's local config to the remote.\n\n",
            "created_at": "2025-06-01T15:27:04Z",
